longBusinessSummary: AMP Limited operates as a wealth management company in Australia and internationally. The company operates through Australian Wealth Management, AMP Bank, AMP Capital, New Zealand Wealth Management, and Australian and New Zealand Wealth Protection and Mature segments. The Australian Wealth Management segment offers financial advice services; platform and software administration services; unit linked superannuation products, including personal and employer sponsored plans with insurance; and retirement income and managed investment products. The AMP Bank segment provides retail banking services covering residential mortgages, deposits, and transaction banking; and a portfolio of practice finance loans. This segment distributes through its aligned distribution network, as well as third party brokers, and direct to retail customers through phone and online. The AMP Capital segment manages investments across various asset classes, including equities, fixed interest, real estate, infrastructure, and multi-manager and multi-asset funds; and provides commercial, industrial, and retail real estate management services. The New Zealand Wealth Management segment provides wealth management solutions comprising KiwiSaver schemes, corporate superannuation, and retail investments, as well as operates a wrap investment management platform. The Australian and New Zealand Wealth Protection and Mature segment offers individual and group term, disability, and income protection insurance products; whole of life, endowment, investment linked, and investment accounts; retirement savings accounts; eligible rollover funds; annuities; insurance bonds; personal superannuation and guaranteed savings accounts; and risk insurance and mature books. AMP Limited was founded in 1849 and is based in Sydney, Australia.
